*Waiting Equals work done*


In real-world delivery operations, not all delays are equal. Some pauses
happen at pickup, some at delivery and each comes with its own operational
cost.

Until now, there was no structured way to define charges that apply
specifically during these waiting periods.

With this update, network owners and managers can set up *Waiting Charges*
that activate exactly when riders are waiting at pickup or delivery, giving
you transparency, control, and fairness across the entire order journey.
[image: image placeholder]
Why We Built This

Previously, waiting time wasn=E2=80=99t explicitly captured in a configurab=
le way.
Riders might spend minutes waiting before a pickup is handed over or before
a customer receives their order and networks had limited ability to account
for these moments.

This led to:

   -

   Uncompensated rider effort
   -

   Hidden operational delays
   -

   Inconsistent pricing scenarios



Now, you can define precise waiting rules for both pickup and delivery
stages making your pricing more aligned with how your operations actually
function.
What=E2=80=99s New


Waiting Charge Types

Users will now see two separate options under Waiting Charges:


*Pickup Waiting Time*

Applicable after the rider *reaches the pickup location* and until *Pickup
Completed*.

This captures scenarios where the merchant takes extra time to hand over
the order.


*Delivery Waiting Time*

Applicable after the rider *reaches the delivery location* and until
*Delivered*.

This accounts for situations where customers delay receiving their package.

Flexible Charging - Time or Status Based

Waiting charges can be defined by:

   -

   *Timeframes* (e.g., first 5 minutes free, charges thereafter)
   -

   *Status windows* (based purely on operational milestones)



You get full control over how waiting time should translate into cost.
What This Means For You

Waiting Charges bring more fairness and clarity to how your network manages
unavoidable delays. With precise control at both pickup and delivery, your
pricing now aligns better with real rider effort.

More refinements are on the way helping you run operations that are smarter
and more efficient than ever.
